<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3818814716" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">“[Hacienda] Huadquina, 5000 ft [= 1524 m|,” southern margin of the Urubamba River, Santa Teresa, Cusco, Peru.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="196" pageNumber="475" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="196.[2065,2658,2904,3326]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">
Taxonomy of A. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1917" box="[2306,2390,3057,3090]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="196" pageNumber="475" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="surdus">surdus</taxonomicName>
is poorly resolved; differentiation from A. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1913" box="[2398,2488,3097,3130]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="196" pageNumber="475" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aerosus">aerosus</taxonomicName>
deserves inspection. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="196" pageNumber="475" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6707438" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6707438" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6707438/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="196" pageNumber="475" targetBox="[1451,2042,2909,3322]" targetPageId="196">
<paragraph blockId="196.[2065,2658,2904,3326]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2065,2241,3175,3208]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">Distribution.</emphasis>
Machu Picchu area in Cusco Department, SE Peru.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="196" pageNumber="475" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="196.[2065,2658,2904,3326]" lastBlockId="196.[1454,2657,3336,3483]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2065,2326,3258,3287]" pageId="196" pageNumber="475">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 110 mm, tail 80 mm, hindfoot 22-5 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Silent Grass Mouse is a moderately small species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1603,1703,3371,3404]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="196" pageNumber="475" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Fur is coarse; dorsum is dark olivaceous gray, slightly contrasting grayish venter; ears are moderatly long; forefeet and hindfeet are grayish brown above but blackish on soles; and tail is relatively long and slightly paler below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="197" pageNumber="476" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="197.[111,1318,296,645]" pageId="197" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,296,329]" pageId="197" pageNumber="476">Habitat.</emphasis>
Restricted to very wet mid-montane forests on steep slopes of the 
<taxonomicName authority="Valley" authorityName="Valley" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Urubamba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="197" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Urubamba Valley</taxonomicName>
at elevations of 600-2000 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
